HEADWORD: Melastoma
<hw>Me*las"to*ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>me`las</grk> black + <grk>sto`ma</grk> mouth.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of evergreen tropical shrubs; -- so
called from the black berries of some species, which stain the
mouth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melastomaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
